Pronunciation[edit]

nŭcleō
  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈnu.kle.oː/, [ˈn̪ʊ.kle.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈnu.kle.o/, [ˈnuː.klɛ.ɔ]
nūcleō
  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈnuː.kle.oː/, [ˈn̪uː.kle.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈnu.kle.o/, [ˈnuː.klɛ.ɔ]

Etymology 1[edit]

nū̆cleus +‎ -ō

Verb[edit]

nū̆cleō (present infinitive nū̆cleāre, perfect active nū̆cleāvī, supine nū̆cleātum); first conjugation

  1. (intransitive) I become kernelly, I become hard like a kernel

Etymology 2[edit]

Regularly declined forms of nū̆cleus.

Noun[edit]

nū̆cleō m

  2. ablative singular of nū̆cleus
